          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="flow-bad" value="❌  HRP = ExpressRoute (default)&#xa;Remote spoke learned via ER (AS-path 12076-12076)&#xa;Spoke→Spoke traffic traverses MSEE &quot;bounce&quot;&#xa;RTT ~46 ms" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FDE7E9;strokeColor=#A4262C;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="80" y="660" width="560" height="90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="flow-good" value="✅  HRP = AS Path&#xa;ER route AS-path shown as 12076-12076-12076 (len 3) — extra 12076 added vs default mode&#xa;H2H AS-path is 65520-65520 (len 2) → H2H wins on shortest AS-path&#xa;Remote spoke next-hop changes to &quot;Remote Hub&quot;. Spoke→Spoke stays on Azure backbone. RTT ~26 ms" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#DFF6DD;strokeColor=#107C10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="720" y="660" width="580" height="90" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ri-note" value="⚠  If your hubs are Secured Hubs (Azure Firewall) you must also configure Routing Intent so private traffic flows through the firewall on the chosen path. HRP decides the path between hubs; Routing Intent decides what inspects it." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF4CE;strokeColor=#8A6D00;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="80" y="770" width="1220" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
